# CLI Usage Guide

The main CLI entry point is [cli.py](mdc:src/i2t/cli.py). It supports the following arguments:

- `image`: Path to the image file (required unless using batch or precache)
- `--model`: Choose between `blip` (default) and `blip-large`
- `--show`: Display the image before captioning
- `--precache`: Download/cache the selected model, then exit
- `--format`: Output format (`text` or `json`)
- `--batch-dir`: Directory for batch image processing
- `--prompt-prefix`: Custom prompt for conditional captioning

See [README.md](mdc:README.md) for example usage and more details.
